text: The Manoir de La Côte is a historic manor in Reugny, Indre-et-Loire, Centre- Val de Loire, France. ==History== It was built in the second half of the 15th century and the 16th century.French Ministry of Culture: Manoir de La Côte It was designed in the Renaissance architectural style. The chapel was built in the 16th century and the dovecote in the 18th century. ==Architectural signifiance== It has been listed as an official historical monument by the French Ministry of Culture since 1989. ==References== Category:Châteaux in Indre-et-Loire Category:Monuments historiques of Indre-et-Loire Category:Renaissance architecture in France
title: Manoir de La Côte
